The eggs, freely laid, are spherical with flexible, thorn-like conical, and very rarely forked, processes (
Fig. 2 F, G
) with diameters of ca. 62 µm excluding processes, and 75–80 µm inclusive. The processes ( 24–26 along the circumference and ca. 100 on the hemisphere) were 7.7–9.1 µm long with a basal diameter of 3.3 –5.0 µm. Some processes have one, or more, transparent basal areas (
Fig. 2 G
). The base of each process is indented (
Fig. 2 G
) but process surface and the egg shell are smooth.
